{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_015cuWzRqVW8ewffRqnpjAJd","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_014zuQMUZe76FRD7jm7gu3pU","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/BLAST_RADIUS.md","content":"# CVE-2021-23337 Blast Radius Analysis: lodash Command Injection\n\n## 1. CVE Identification\n\n| Field | Detail |\n|-------|--------|\n| **CVE ID** | CVE-2021-23337 |\n| **Package** | lodash (npm) |\n| **Vulnerability** | Command injection via the `_.template` function — the `sourceURL` option is passed unsanitized to `Function()`, allowing arbitrary code execution when attacker-controlled input reaches `_.template` |\n| **Vulnerable range** | `< 4.17.21` (all versions prior to the patch) |\n| **Fixed version** | `4.17.21` |\n| **CVSS** | 7.2 (High) |\n\n---\n\n## 2. Direct Dependents\n\nThe following manifest files declare lodash as a direct dependency:\n\n### `/workspace/lodash/package.json`\n- **Package**: `lodash` (version `4.17.20`) — this IS the lodash package itself\n- **devDependency**: `\"lodash\": \"4.17.14\"` (pinned exact version, used for self-testing)\n\n### `/workspace/webpack/package.json`\n- **Package**: `webpack` (version `5.64.0`)\n- **devDependency**: `\"lodash\": \"^4.17.19\"`\n- **devDependency**: `\"lodash-es\": \"^4.17.15\"`\n\n### `/workspace/jest/examples/manual-mocks/package.json`\n- **Package**: `example-manual-mocks`\n- **dependency**: `\"lodash\": \"^4.17.19\"`\n\nNo lodash direct dependency was found in any `jest` monorepo package under `jest/packages/*/package.json`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Transitive Dependency Paths\n\n### 3.1 `/workspace/lodash` (package-lock.json — npm)\n\nThe following packages transitively pull lodash into the lodash repo's own dev environment:\n\n| Package | Requires lodash | Resolved version | Hops |\n|---------|----------------|-----------------|------|\n| `async` | `^4.17.14` | 4.17.14 | 1 |\n| `babel-core` | `^4.17.4` | 4.17.14 | 1 |\n| `babel-generator` | `^4.17.4` | 4.17.14 | 1 |\n| `babel-helper-define-map` | `^4.17.4` | 4.17.14 | 1 |\n| `babel-helper-regex` | `^4.17.4` | 4.17.14 | 1 |\n| `babel-plugin-transform-es2015-block-scoping` | `^4.17.4` | 4.17.14 | 1 |\n| `babel-register` | `^4.17.4` | 4.17.14 | 1 |\n| `babel-template` | `^4.17.4` | 4.17.14 | 1 |\n| `babel-traverse` | `^4.17.4` | 4.17.14 | 1 |\n| `babel-types` | `^4.17.4` | 4.17.14 | 1 |\n| `benchmark` | `^4.17.4` | 4.17.14 | 1 |\n| `docdown` | `^4.17.5` | 4.17.14 | 1 |\n| `lodash-doc-globals` | `^4.16.0` | 4.17.14 | 1 |\n| `jscs` | `~3.10.0` | **3.10.1** | 1 |\n| `jsdoctypeparser` | `^3.7.0` | **3.10.1** | 1 |\n| `xmlbuilder` | `^3.5.0` | **3.10.1** | 1 |\n\n> Note: `jscs`, `jsdoctypeparser`, and `xmlbuilder` pull lodash **v3.x**, a separate vulnerable branch.\n\n### 3.2 `/workspace/webpack` (yarn.lock — Yarn v1)\n\n| Package | Requires lodash | Resolved version | Hops |\n|---------|----------------|-----------------|------|\n| `webpack` (direct devDep) | `^4.17.19` | 4.17.21 | 0 |\n| `@typescript-eslint/typescript-estree@4.8.2` | `^4.17.15` | 4.17.21 | 1 |\n| `benchmark` | `^4.17.4` | 4.17.21 | 1 |\n| `eslint-plugin-jsdoc` | `^4.17.21` | 4.17.21 | 1 |\n| `json-schema-to-typescript` | `^4.17.15` | 4.17.21 | 1 |\n| `whatwg-url` | `^4.7.0` | 4.17.21 | 1 |\n\nTransitive chain example:\n```\nwebpack (devDep) -> eslint-plugin-jsdoc -> lodash@4.17.21\nwebpack (devDep) -> @typescript-eslint/typescript-estree -> lodash@4.17.21\n```\n\n### 3.3 `/workspace/jest` (yarn.lock — Yarn Berry/v2+)\n\n| Package | Requires lodash | Resolved version | Hops |\n|---------|----------------|-----------------|------|\n| `example-manual-mocks` (direct dep) | `^4.17.19` | 4.17.21 | 0 |\n| `@babel/core@7.12.9` | `^4.17.19` | 4.17.21 | 1 |\n| `@docusaurus/core` | `^4.17.21` | 4.17.21 | 1 |\n| `@docusaurus/plugin-client-redirects` | `^4.17.21` | 4.17.21 | 1 |\n| `@microsoft/api-extractor` | `~4.17.15` | 4.17.21 | 1 |\n| `@react-native-community/cli-platform-android` | `^4